column5:
Convert StringValuePtr to either RSTRING_PTR or StringValueCStr

Where a simple nul-terminated C string is required, use StringValueCStr.
Where a string pointer and length are used, follow the pattern:

  Check_Type(str, T_STRING);
  ptr = RSTRING_PTR(str);
  len = RSTRING_LEN(str);

Allow read connection defaults from custom default file and group. #262

For example:
@client = Mysql2::Client.new(:default_file => "/user/.my.cnf", :default_group => "client")
